[3] Cholera - India (Maharashtra)
Date: Mon 28 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ArabNews.com [edited]
<http://www.arabnews.com/?page=4Â§ion=0&article=61185&d=28&m=3&y=2005>

Outbreak of cholera in Maharashtra districts
-----------------------------------------------
The state government, responding to a cholera and gastroenteritis outbreak
in Pune and Sangli districts, launched an emergency operation to battle and
control the epidemic.
In all, 500 cholera and gastroenteritis patients in Sangli were admitted to
several government and private hospitals for treatment.
The state health authorities have launched a door-to-door awareness
program, educating people in epidemic-affected places on prevention
measures, checking people for jaundice symptoms [there is a concurrent
hepatitis outbreak in the state of Majarashtra - see ProMED-mail posting
Hepatitis - India (Maharashtra): RFI 20050328.0898 - Mod.MPP], and
providing information about medical and water purification centers.
[Byline: Shahid Raza Burney]
